 Port Elizabeth - A joint operation between SAPS Kwazakele Vispol Task Team and the Motherwell Cluster Serious and Violent Crime Investigation Unit resulted in the arrest of two suspects allegedly involved in the murder and robbery of a prominent Zwide resident as well as the attempted murder and vehicle hijacking of two other people on Christmas Eve. "It is alleged that on the mentioned date, at about 17:10, Peter Sample (62) was fatally wounded while he was working in his garage at his house in Higa Street in Zwide," said police spokesperson, Col Priscilla Naidu. "Three unknown males came to the house alleging that he bought stolen speakers. "The men left and later returned and shot Sample twice in his head. "They left with his TV set." Col Naidu said that as the suspects exited the house, they saw a red Bantam bakkie was passing by. "The suspects shot at the vehicle, injuring the driver in his left hand and his passenger (wife) in her right foot. They got out of the bakkie and the suspects took the bakkie and left." Peter Sample was an anti-apartheid activist, who once spent time on Robben Island. On Monday, the teams followed up on information on the possible whereabouts of the suspects. "The suspects were seen walking in Saba Street, Kwazakele. A foot chase ensued and both suspects, aged 26 and 28 years old, were arrested." They are detained on charges of murder, house robbery, attempted murder (x2) and carjacking. They are expected to appear in court soon. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 